   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to John Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, 1863 December 15</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated December 15, 1863, from John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to John Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, Watkins describes the Confederate siege of Knoxville and the assault on Fort Sanders, which he refers to as "the fort on the west side of town." The death of General William P. Sanders is mentioned: "Gen'l Sanders was mortally wounded while leading a charge on the rebel rifle pits, died the next night."</abstract>
